🏠 House Price Prediction using Machine Learning
📌 Overview

This project is a machine learning-based house price prediction system built using Python. It uses a Random Forest Regressor to predict house prices based on features like area, bedrooms, bathrooms, age, and location.

🚀 Features
Data preprocessing using Pandas
Categorical encoding (One-Hot Encoding)
Model training using Random Forest
Model evaluation using R² Score
Data visualization (Area vs Price)
User input-based real-time prediction

🛠️ Technologies Used
Python
Pandas
Matplotlib
Scikit-learn

📂 Project Structure
├── code.py              # Main Python script
├── house_data.csv      # Dataset file
├── README.md           # Project documentation

📊 Dataset

The dataset contains the following features:

area – Size of the house
bedrooms – Number of bedrooms
bathrooms – Number of bathrooms
age – Age of the property
location – (urban / suburban / rural)
price – Target variable

📈 Model
Algorithm: Random Forest Regressor
Train-Test Split: 80% training, 20% testing
Evaluation Metric: R² Score

📉 Visualization
The project generates a scatter plot:
Area vs Price

🎯 How It Works
Loads dataset from CSV
Converts categorical data into numerical format
Splits data into training and testing sets
Trains the model
Evaluates accuracy
Takes user input
Predicts house price

🧪 Example Input
Enter area: 1200
Enter bedrooms: 3
Enter bathrooms: 2
Enter age: 5
Enter location: urban
📌 Output
Predicted House Price: XXXXX

⚠️ Limitations
Dataset is small → accuracy may be misleading
No feature scaling or tuning. 

